
*******************************************************************************

 Your GWT client has been generated.
 
*******************************************************************************
 
 Here's your checklist:
 
 1) Run your migrations to synchronize the state of your GWT models and
    your REST resources:
 
    > rake db:migrate
 
 2) Compile down to JavaScript:
 
    > rake gwt:compile
 
 3) Test:
 
    > rake start
    ... visit http://localhost:3000/ui in your browser.
    
 Other things you can do:
 
 * Generate a new GWT model that stays in sync with your server-side schema.
   For example, an "action item" with a "name" property:
 
    > script/generate gwt_resource ActionItem name:string
    > rake db:migrate
    
 * Generate a desktop version of your application using Adobe AIR.
   For example, to generate an app called ToDoList with a unique ID
   of com.yourcompany.ToDoList:
 
    > script/generate air_client ToDoList --app-id=com.yourcompany.ToDoList
    > rake air:debug
      or
    > rake air:package
 
*******************************************************************************

